snippet: As Augusta National Golf Club opened for official Masters practice rounds, many fans rushed to where the so-called Eisenhower tree stood until it was lost this year to a storm.
abstract: Augusta National Golf Club opens for official Masters practice rounds and many fans rush to where the so-called Eisenhower Tree stood until it was lost this year to a storm; fairway has healed beautifully, though circular scar remains visible from tree's removal in February 2014.
lead_paragraph: As Augusta National Golf Club opened for official Masters practice rounds, many fans rushed to where the so-called Eisenhower tree stood until it was lost this year to a storm.

headline.main: After Pine’s Removal, Fans Miss a Tree That a President Often Didn’t
headline.print_headline: After Pine’s Removal, Fans Miss a Hazard a President Did Not
